<h2>Glider Shuttles</h2>

<p>The <a href="guns.html">p216 gun</a> uses a variety of different
p24-glider interactions, but there is one more 180-degree turn that
I didn't use. Here is a period-120 shuttle that shows it off:</p>

<div align="CENTER"><a href="p120-shuttle.lif"><img src= 
"p120-shuttle.gif" width="147" height="75" alt=
"p120 shuttle"></a></div>

<p>One can also base shuttles on reflections from other
oscillators; Dean found this family of period 24+30n shuttles based
on a p3 turn.</p>

<div align="CENTER"><a href="p3-shuttles.lif"><img src= 
"p3-shuttles.gif" width="283" height="163" alt=
"p24,p54,p84 shuttles"></a></div>

